The community is referring to Eurélia Manuel Benjamim as having been resurrected from the dead, but she says she had just gone away to work on her uncle’s farm for a few months. A local administrator in Montepuez district told the state broadcaster: “They conducted all the funeral ceremonies, the funeral, third day ceremony and visiting the grave and the grave has not been breached.” A team of experts is being sent to Lindi to investigate to see who or what was buried in the grave. --BBC--